  "hypothesis": "Dual momentum combining absolute momentum (ETF 21-day return > 0) with relative momentum (cross-sectional ranking) across 8 liquid ETFs. Critical fix from iterations 3 and 6: trade count has been catastrophically low (12-23 trades) due to either infrequent rebalancing OR overly restrictive trend filters. This iteration uses DAILY rebalancing (rebalance_days=1) to maximize trade frequency, holds top 3 ETFs simultaneously by 21-day return, and replaces the 200-day MA filter with a simpler absolute momentum filter (return > 0). Daily rebalancing on 8 ETFs holding top 3 should generate ~252 rebalances \u00d7 ~1 trade per rebalance day (position changes) = 100-300 trades over the 5-year IS period. The 21-day lookback (1 month) captures meaningful momentum while being responsive enough for daily rebalancing. Long-only avoids short-side losses (iter 4 failure). No MA filter avoids signal suppression (iter 6 failure). Absolute momentum filter (return > 0) prevents buying into downtrends without being as restrictive as the 200-day MA.",
